- @html_id = "home"
.container
  .row
    #happy-path
      .content.start
        .page-header
          %h1 
            = I18n.t("site_name")
            %br
            %small
              = I18n.t("tag_line")
        .row.start-now
          .span5
            = form_tag anonymous_user_registration_path, :class => "form-stracked" do
              %p
                %button.success.btn.large Create Checklist Now
              %p Try the app anonymously. Especially the keyboard interaction. If you like what you see, your checklists will be saved to your account when you sign up.
              %p Open Hercules is free and <a href="https://github.com/flyingmachine/openhercules">open source</a>.

      .content.sign_up
        .row
          .span5
            %h3 Sign up

            %p Access your lists from any browser &bull; Create private lists &bull; Privately share your lists with other users

            = form_tag user_registration_path, :class => "form-stacked" do
              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_email"} Email
                .input#user_email= text_field_tag 'user[email]', ""

              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_username"} Username
                .input#user_email= text_field_tag 'user[username]', ""


              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_password"} Password
                .input#user_password= password_field_tag 'user[password]', ""

              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_password_confirmation"} Password Confirmation
                .input#user_password= password_field_tag 'user[password_confirmation]', ""

              .clearfix
                %input.primary.btn{:type => "submit", :value => "Sign up"}

      .content.log_in
        .row
          .span5
            %h3 Log in
            = form_tag user_session_path, :class => "form-stacked" do
              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_username"} Username
                .input#user_email= text_field_tag 'user[username]', ""

              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_password"} Password
                .input#user_password= password_field_tag 'user[password]', ""

              .clearfix
                %label{:for => "user_remember_me"}
                  = check_box_tag 'user[remember_me]', 'true', false, :id => "user_remember_me"
                  Remember Me

              .clearfix= link_to "Forgot your password?", new_password_path('user')

              .clearfix
                %input.primary.btn{:type => "submit", :value => "Log in"}
                  
      .content.features
        .row
          .span5
            %h3 How's This Different?

            %h4 It's keyboard friendly
            %p Thanks to smart key bindings, you can edit your lists without touching your mouse.

            %h4 It's social
            %p You can share your lists publicly, spreading your knowledge far and wide.

            %h4 Cloning is easy
            %p If you find a list that you like, you can easily clone it and make it your own. For example, if you like this <a href="/lists/4f6cb05b6680b50001000001">travel checklist</a>, you can just clone it and modify it to your heart's content.
            %p This also makes it easy to reuse your own lists.

            %h4 It's Free
            %p Completely free. No fee for using it. It's <a href="https://github.com/flyingmachine/openhercules">open source</a>, too, so you can install it on your company's intranet or modify it or sell it on the black market or whatever.

      .content.name
        .row
          .span5
            %h3 About the Name
            %p <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hercules">Hercules</a> had probably the worst todo list ever imagined:
            %ul
              %li Kill the Nemean lion
              %li Destroy the Lernaean Hydra
              %li Capture the Ceryneian Hind alive
              %li Trap the Erymanthian boar
              %li Clean the Augean stables
              %li Butcher the Stymphalian birds
              %li Capture the Cretan bull
              %li Round up the Mares of Diomedes
              %li Fetch Hippolyta's girdle of gold
              %li Fetch the cattle of Geryon
              %li Fetch the golden apples of the Hesperides
              %li Bring Cerberus from Tartarus
            %p ... and he managed to get that stuff done.
